You can save an array into your Firestore database normally, just by doing something like 

    this.db.collection([YOUR_COLLECTION]).add({link: [YOUR_ARRAY]});

where `[YOUR_ARRAY]` contains your download urls. This way you will create one Firestore document containing a field called `link` that is an array of your urls. This document will have an automatically generated ID; if you want to give yourself an id to your document, you would want to do something like this:

    this.db.collection([YOUR_COLLECTION]).doc([YOUR_DOCUMENT]).set({link: arr});

In terms of having that array in ascending order, you will need to organize it first as you wish before you add it.

